<Base title="About · AI Evolution Tree">
  <article class="prose-node max-w-none">
    <h1>About AI Evolution Tree</h1>
    <p>
      <strong>AI Evolution Tree</strong> is an open, community-curated tree of every
      meaningful advancement in machine learning, deep learning, and AI. The
      tree is ordered by time (older work at the top, newer at the bottom) and
      structured by intellectual lineage — each node lists the prior work it
      builds on.
    </p>

    <h2>Why two views</h2>
    <p>
      The biggest gap in AI literacy is that technical writing is too dense for
      investors, operators, and curious newcomers, while explainer content is
      too vague for builders. Each node here ships <em>both</em> layers from the
      same canonical record, so a hedge fund analyst and an ML engineer can
      stand on the same facts.
    </p>

    <h2>How to contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Read <a href="https://github.com/aievolutiontree/aievolutiontree/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>,
      copy <code>src/content/nodes/_template.mdx</code>, fill in the schema,
      open a pull request. Every merge is permanent attribution.
    </p>

    <h2>Licensing</h2>
